<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">N/M - Not Meaningful</font></div>
<div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">
<tr valign="top">
<td align="right" style="WIDTH: 54pt">
<div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">(a)&#160;&#160;</font></div></td>
<td>
<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">See (a) on previous table.</font></div></td></tr></table></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Note:&#160;&#160;Certain 2008 sales details have been reclassified to conform to current period presentation.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Pharmaceutical</font></font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Global sales of our pharmaceutical products decreased 4.4% during the three months ended June 30, 2009.&#160;&#160;The effect of unfavorable exchange rates decreased global sales of our pharmaceutical products 6.0%.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange fluctuations, our sales
of pharmaceutical products would have grown 1.6%.&#160;&#160;Sales of our glaucoma and otic products reflected volume gains.&#160;&#160;These gains were substantially offset by the loss of patent protection for <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> suspension and contraction in the ocular allergy market.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Our line of glaucoma products includes <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TRAVATAN</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> ophthalmic solution, <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TRAVATAN Z</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174; </font>ophthalmic
solution and <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">DuoTrav</font>&#8482; ophthalmic solution.&#160;&#160;<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TRAVATAN</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Z</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> enables doctors to help glaucoma patients with a benzalkonium chloride ("BAC") free prostaglandin analogue
formation.&#160;&#160;<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">DuoTrav</font>&#8482; is a combination of the prostaglandin analogue travoprost in <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TRAVATAN</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> with the beta blocker timolol and is marketed in several European Union countries, Canada and Australia.&#160;&#160;Combined sales of our family of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TRAVATAN</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> products
grew 15.4% for the three months ended June 30, 2009, reflecting share and volume growth in the United States and the International business segments.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div></div>
<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">31</font></div>
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160; </font></div></div>
<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div></div></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>During the three months ended June 30, 2009, <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Azopt</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> ophthalmic suspension, the Company's topical carbonic anhydrase inhibitor, posted a 3.7% sales increase.&#160;&#160;The
introduction of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Azarga</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top; FONT-STYLE: italic">&#174;</font> ophthalmic suspension in Europe, subsequent to its approval in late 2008, has been well received.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>Sales of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Vigamox</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> ophthalmic solution, our leading anti-infective fluoroquinolone drug, increased 15.3% compared to 2008, reflecting global volume growth
and price increases.&#160;&#160;(Moxifloxacin<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">, </font>the primary ingredient in <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Vigamox</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font>, is licensed to Alcon by Bayer HealthCare AG.)&#160;&#160;<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">NEVANAC</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> ophthalmic suspension is our
non-steroidal anti-inflammatory drug ("NSAID") for the treatment of pain and inflammation associated with cataract surgery.&#160;&#160;Sales of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">NEVANAC</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> grew 17.0% in the three months ended June 30, 2009 over the same period of the prior year, primarily from growth outside the United States.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Pursuant to a prior legal settlement, a competitor of Alcon&#8217;s launched a generic version of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> ophthalmic suspension on January 1, 2009.&#160;&#160;Falcon
Pharmaceuticals, our generic pharmaceutical subsidiary, also launched a generic version of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> suspension on January 2, 2009.&#160;&#160;During the three months ended June 30, 2009, sales of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> ophthalmic suspension, our
branded combination drug for the treatment of infection and inflammation, decreased 60.1% globally, primarily within the United States, over the same period of 2008.&#160;&#160;We expect that these generic products will result in a decline of our sales and profits for <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> for 2009.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Contraction in the global allergy markets resulted in a combined decline for global sales of our leading allergy products, <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Patanol</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> and <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Pataday</font>&#8482;
ophthalmic solutions in the three months ended June 30, 2009.&#160;&#160;However, we continued to expand market share in the contracting markets.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Sales of otic/nasal products were flat in the three months ended June 30, 2009, compared to the same period of 2008, despite contraction in the market for otic products.&#160;&#160;Sales of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">CIPRODEX</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174; </font>otic
suspension were positively influenced by market share gains, which offset a decrease in U.S. otic market volume during 2009.&#160;&#160;(<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">CIPRODEX</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> is a registered trademark of Bayer AG, licensed to Alcon by Bayer HealthCare AG.)&#160;&#160;Sales in 2008 reflected the initial distribution and U.S. launch of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Patanase</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top; FONT-STYLE: italic">&#174;</font> nasal
spray in May 2008.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>The change in the other pharmaceuticals/rebates line for the period ended June 30, 2009, compared to 2008, primarily reflects growth in rebates under the U.S. Medicaid program attributable to increasing utilization rates and higher statutory discounts.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Surgical</font></font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Global sales of our surgical products declined 1.4% to $757 million in the three months ended June 30, 2009, compared to 2008.&#160;&#160;The effect of unfavorable exchange rates decreased global sales of our surgical products 7.5%.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange fluctuations,
our sales of surgical products would have increased 6.1%.&#160;&#160;Higher sales of advanced technology intraocular lenses, monofocal intraocular lenses and cataract and vitreoretinal products (which include surgical equipment, devices and disposable products) accounted for the constant currency growth.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Sales of intraocular lenses increased 0.3% in the three months ended June 30, 2009 over the same period in 2008.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange fluctuations, intraocular lens sales would have increased 8.7%.&#160;&#160;We continued to see some pressure on cataract procedures
and advanced technology intraocular lenses due to global economic conditions.&#160;&#160;Reported global sales of our advanced technology lenses increased 30.1% in the three months ended June 30, 2009 and would have grown 38.3%, without the 8.2% negative effect of foreign exchange fluctuations.&#160;&#160;Our advanced technology lenses include the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174; </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">ReSTOR</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> multifocal
intraocular lens that corrects presbyopia and the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174; </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Toric</font> intraocular lens that corrects pre-existing astigmatism.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Sales of other surgical products were adversely impacted by exchange rates but grew faster on a constant currency basis in the international markets due to growth of phaco surgery in emerging markets, increased acceptance of advanced technology products and the introduction of products in
additional markets.&#160;&#160;The solid constant currency sales growth came from most major product categories within the cataract and vitreoretinal segments.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div></div>
<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">32</font></div>
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160; </font></div></div>
<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div></div></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Refractive sales declined 9.7% to $28 million for the three months ended June 30, 2009.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange fluctuations, refractive sales for 2009 would have decreased 3.2%, primarily as a result of global economic conditions.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Consumer Eye Care</font></font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Our global consumer eye care sales, consisting of contact lens care solutions, artificial tears and other general eye care products, decreased 6.8% to $207 million in the three months ended June 30, 2009, compared to $222 million in the three months ended June 30, 2008.&#160;&#160;The effect of unfavorable exchange rates decreased global
sales of our consumer eye care products 6.3%.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange fluctuations, our sales of consumer eye care products would have decreased 0.5%.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Sales of our contact lens disinfectants declined 5.7% in the three months ended June 30, 2009 compared to the same period in 2008.&#160;&#160;Excluding the impact of foreign exchange, sales of contact lens care disinfectants decreased 2.4%, due primarily to a decline in the market for branded multi-purpose solutions, changes in retailer purchasing
patterns and competitive pressures.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Sales of our artificial tears products, including </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic">Systane</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"> and </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic">Systane</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic">Ultra </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">lubricant
eye drops, would have grown 10.0% on a constant currency basis, compared to the same period in 2008, primarily due to volume and price gains. A portion of the improvement was due to the launch of </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic">Systane</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic">Ultra</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"> in
the United States in</font> <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">July 2008.</font>&#160;&#160;<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">The 10.0% negative effect attributable to foreign exchange fluctuations held reported sales of our artificial tears products flat over 2008.</font></font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Gross Profit</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Gross profit decreased 4.5% to $1,262 million in the three months ended June 30, 2009 from $1,321 million in 2008.&#160;&#160;Gross profit decreased as a percent of sales to 75.3% in the three months ended June 30, 2009 from 76.1% in 2008.&#160;&#160;Gross profit margin declined as a result of the loss of gross margin on sales of tobramycin/dexamethasone
combination products from generic competition to <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top; FONT-STYLE: italic">&#174; </font>and the effect of differences in foreign currency exchange rates between the second quarters of 2009 and 2008.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Operating Expenses</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Selling, general and administrative expenses decreased 11.2% to $468 million in the three months ended June 30, 2009 from $527 million in 2008.&#160;&#160;Selling, general and administrative expenses decreased as a percentage of sales to 27.9% from 30.4% in 2008.&#160;&#160;The decrease in expenses reflected the favorable effects of foreign
currency fluctuations, lower share-based payments expense, labor savings from the 2009 workforce reduction and disciplined cost management programs.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Research and development expenses increased 10.6% to $157 million (or 9.4% of sales) in the three months ended June 30, 2009 from $142 million (or 8.2% of sales) in 2008.&#160;&#160;The increase in research and development expenses represented a continued investment across pharmaceutical, surgical and consumer eye care product lines.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Operating Income</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Operating income decreased 2.2% to $632 million in the three months ended June 30, 2009 from $646 million in 2008.&#160;&#160;This decline in 2009 reflected the decrease in gross profit that was partially offset by decreased operating expenses discussed above.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Alcon United States business segment operating income increased 8.7% to $475 million, or 60.1% of sales, in the three months ended June 30, 2009 from $437 million, or 55.4% of sales, in 2008.&#160;&#160;Operating income as a percent of sales improved in 2009 primarily as a result of disciplined cost management programs.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Alcon International business segment operating income decreased 6.3% to $372 million, or 41.9% of sales, in the three months ended June 30, 2009 from $397 million, or 41.9% of sales in 2008.&#160;&#160;In 2009, the operating income </font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160;</font></div>
<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div></div>
<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">33</font></div>
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160; </font></div></div>
<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">margin remained flat as result of the temporary effect of differences in foreign currency exchange rates on gross margins between the second quarters of 2009 and 2008 that offset improved operating expense margins.</font></div></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Operating income for the Alcon United States and Alcon International business segments does not include: (1) certain manufacturing costs (e.g., manufacturing operation period costs and manufacturing variances); (2) research and development costs other than regulatory costs; (3) certain other general corporate expenses; and (4) share-based
compensation.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Interest and Other Income (Expenses)</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Interest income decreased 35.0% to $13 million in the three months ended June 30, 2009 from $20 million in 2008, primarily as a result of lower short term interest rates, partially offset by higher balances of cash and cash equivalents in 2009.&#160;&#160;Interest expense decreased 64.3% to $5 million in the three months ended June 30, 2009
from $14 million in 2008, resulting from lower borrowings and decreased interest<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;</font>rates.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Other, net, included gains (losses) on investments for the three months ended June 30, 2009 and 2008 as follows:</font></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Total</font></div></td>
<td align="right" valign="bottom" width="1%" style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4px"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></td>
<td valign="bottom" width="1%" style="BORDER-BOTTOM: black 4px double; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">$</font></td>
<td valign="bottom" width="9%" style="BORDER-BOTTOM: black 4px double; TEXT-ALIGN: right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">2</font></td>
<td nowrap valign="bottom" width="1%" style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4px; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></td>
<td align="right" valign="bottom" width="1%" style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4px"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></td>
<td valign="bottom" width="1%" style="BORDER-BOTTOM: black 4px double; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">$</font></td>
<td valign="bottom" width="9%" style="BORDER-BOTTOM: black 4px double; TEXT-ALIGN: right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">1</font></td>
<td nowrap valign="bottom" width="1%" style="PADDING-BOTTOM: 4px; TEXT-ALIGN: left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160;</font></td></tr></table></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Alcon and its subsidiaries invest cash generated from operations to fund ongoing operating expenses, research and development and long term corporate liabilities.&#160;&#160;The majority of the funds needed to accommodate expenses and liabilities are invested in cash and cash equivalents, the income from which is recorded in interest income.&#160;&#160;The
Company's long term liabilities are evaluated with the help of outside consultants and are offset by a portfolio of investments with similar durations and appropriate hurdle rates.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Despite the significant weighting to cash, the Company had material exposure during the first two quarters of 2009 and 2008 to the following investment markets: fixed income securities, hedge funds, senior secured bank loans funds and equities.&#160;&#160;The Company has requested redemption of its investments in hedge funds and expects to
receive the majority of those proceeds throughout 2009.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Income Tax Expense</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Income tax expense decreased to $69 million in the three months ended June 30, 2009 from $83 million in the same period of 2008.&#160;&#160;The effective tax rate was 10.6% in the three months ended June 30, 2009, compared to 12.8% in the three months ended June 30, 2008.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">The 10.6% effective tax rate for the three months ended June 30, 2009 reflected the combined effects of (i) differences in product and geographic earnings mix, including a larger share of research and development funding from the United States, (ii) the Swiss tax benefits associated with the expansion of the Company&#8217;s global administration
operations in Switzerland, (iii) the passage of the research and experimentation credit in the fourth quarter of 2008 and (iv) period items related to audit settlements, APA negotiations, the lapse of statutes of limitations and other minor items.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Net Earnings</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Net earnings increased 2.6% to $582 million in the three months ended June 30, 2009 from $567 million in 2008.&#160;&#160;This increase resulted from 2009 gains from reductions in selling, general and administrative expenses, foreign currency changes and reductions in income taxes.</font></div>
<br>
<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160; </font></div></div>
<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">34</font></div>
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160; </font></div></div>
<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160; </font></div></div></div>
<br>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Six months ended June 30, 2009 compared to six months ended June 30, 2008</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>The following discussion compares operations for the six months ended June 30, 2009 to operations for the six months ended June 30, 2008.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Sales</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>The Company's global sales decreased 3.1% to $3,170 million for the six months ended June 30, 2009 from the same period in 2008.&#160;&#160;The effect of unfavorable exchange rates decreased global sales 7.2%.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange fluctuations, global sales would
have grown 4.1%, primarily reflecting volume growth during the three months ended June 30, 2009.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>

<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">4.1</font></div></td>

<td valign="top" width="1%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160; </font></td></tr></table></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">
<tr valign="top">
<td align="right" style="WIDTH: 45pt">
<div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">(a)&#160;&#160;</font></div></td>
<td>
<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Change in constant currency (as referenced throughout this discussion) is determined by comparing adjusted 2009 reported amounts, calculated using 2008 monthly average exchange rates, to the actual 2008 reported amounts.&#160;&#160;Sales change in constant currency is not a U.S. GAAP defined measure of revenue growth.&#160;&#160;Change in constant currency
calculates sales growth without the impact of foreign exchange fluctuations.&#160;&#160;Management believes constant currency sales growth is an important measure of the Company&#8217;s operations because it provides investors with a clearer picture of the core rate of sales growth attributable to changes in unit volumes and local currency prices.&#160;&#160;Sales change in constant currency, as defined and presented by the Company, may not be comparable to similar measures reported by other companies.</font></div></td></tr></table></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Alcon United States sales decreased 0.8% to $1,448 million for the six months ended June 30, 2009, from $1,460 million for the comparable period in 2008.&#160;&#160;The decrease was mostly due to generic competition to <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> suspension,
lower market prescription volumes, lower cataract equipment sales and changes in retailer purchasing patterns in the consumer products.&#160;&#160;These factors were partially offset by market share gains in several product categories, including increased sales of advanced technology intraocular lenses and glaucoma products.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Alcon International sales decreased 5.0% to $1,722 million in the six months ended June 30, 2009, from $1,812 million in the same period of 2008.&#160;&#160;The effect of unfavorable exchange rates decreased Alcon International sales 13.0%.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange
fluctuations, Alcon International sales would have grown 8.0%, reflecting volume growth during the period.&#160;&#160;International sales grew on a constant currency basis across all product </font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160;</font></div>
<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div></div>
<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">35</font></div>
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160; </font></div></div>
<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div></div></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">lines.&#160;&#160;Pharmaceutical sales growth in Japan and the organic sales growth in emerging markets were the main contributors to this performance.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">

<td align="left" valign="top" width="27%">
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">Total Global Sales</font></div></td>
<td align="right" valign="top" width="1%" style="BORDER-BOTTOM: black 4px double">
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">$</font></div></td>
<td align="right" valign="top" width="6%" style="BORDER-BOTTOM: black 4px double">
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">3,170</font></div></td>
<td valign="top" width="1%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160; </font></td>
<td align="right" valign="top" width="1%" style="BORDER-BOTTOM: black 4px double">
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">$</font></div></td>
<td align="right" valign="top" width="6%" style="BORDER-BOTTOM: black 4px double">
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">3,272</font></div></td>
<td valign="top" width="1%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160; </font></td>
<td valign="top" width="1%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160; </font></td>
<td align="right" valign="top" width="6%">
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(3.1</font></div></td>
<td align="left" valign="top" width="1%">
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">)</font></div></td>
<td valign="top" width="1%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160; </font></td>
<td align="right" valign="top" width="7%">
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">(7.2</font></div></td>
<td align="left" valign="top" width="2%">
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">)</font></div></td>
<td valign="top" width="1%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160; </font></td>
<td align="right" valign="top" width="8%">
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="right"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">4.1</font></div></td>
<td valign="top" width="2%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160; </font></td>
<td valign="top" width="1%"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">&#160; </font></td></tr></table></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">N/M - Not Meaningful</font></div>
<div>
<table cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" id="list" width="100%" style="FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: times new roman">
<tr valign="top">
<td align="right" style="WIDTH: 45pt">
<div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">(a)&#160;&#160;</font></div></td>
<td>
<div style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">See (a) on previous table.</font></div></td></tr></table></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 27pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Note:&#160;&#160;Certain 2008 sales details have been reclassified to conform to current period presentation.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Pharmaceutical</font></font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Global sales of our pharmaceutical products decreased 2.5% during the six months ended June 30, 2009.&#160;&#160;The effect of unfavorable exchange rates decreased global sales of our pharmaceutical products 6.1%.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange fluctuations, our sales
of pharmaceutical products would have grown 3.6%.&#160;&#160;Sales of key products in most major therapeutic categories reflected volume gains and share growth.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Our line of glaucoma products includes <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TRAVATAN</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font>, <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TRAVATAN Z</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174; </font>and <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">DuoTrav</font>&#8482;.&#160;&#160;Even
including the effects of foreign exchange, combined sales of our family of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TRAVATAN</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> products grew 17.0% for the six months ended June 30, 2009, reflecting growth in the United States and the International business segments.&#160;&#160;During the six months ended June 30, 2009, <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Azopt</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> posted
a 4.1% sales increase.&#160;&#160;The introduction of Azarga<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174; </font>in Europe, subsequent to its approval in late 2008, has been well received.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 36pt"></font>Sales of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Vigamox</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font>, our leading anti-infective fluoroquinolone drug, increased 0.9% compared to 2008 (2.2% excluding the 1.3% negative effect of foreign
exchange fluctuations), reflecting volume growth outside the United States.&#160;&#160;Sales of anti-inflammatory <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">NEVANAC</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> grew 11.4% in the six months ended June 30, 2009 over the same period of the prior year, due primarily to new product registrations outside the United States.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div></div>
<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">36</font></div>
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160; </font></div></div>
<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div></div></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font id="TAB1" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 14.4pt"></font>Pursuant to a prior legal settlement, a competitor of Alcon&#8217;s launched a generic version of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> ophthalmic suspension on January 1, 2009.&#160;&#160;Falcon
Pharmaceuticals, our generic pharmaceutical subsidiary, also launched a generic version of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> suspension on January 2, 2009.&#160;&#160;During the six months ended June 30, 2009, sales of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> ophthalmic suspension, our
branded combination drug for the treatment of infection and inflammation, decreased 57.0% globally, primarily within the United States, over the same period of 2008.&#160;&#160;We expect that these generic products will result in a decline of our sales and profits for <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">TobraDex</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174; </font>for 2009.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Despite contraction in the U.S. allergy market, global sales of our leading allergy products, <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Patanol</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> and <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Pataday</font>&#8482;, grew 2.3% in the six
months ended June 30, 2009.&#160;&#160;The increase in sales reflected growth outside the United States during the first quarter of 2009; however, we continued to expand market share in the contracting U.S. market.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Sales of otic/nasal products increased 5.3% in the six months ended June 30, 2009 over the same period of 2008, despite contraction in the market for otic products.&#160;&#160;Sales of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">CIPRODEX</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174; </font>otic
suspension were positively influenced by market share gains, which offset a decrease in U.S. otic market volume during 2009.&#160;&#160;Sales in 2008 included the initial distribution and U.S. launch of <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Patanase</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top; FONT-STYLE: italic">&#174;</font> nasal spray in May 2008.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">The change in the other pharmaceuticals/rebates line for the period ended June 30, 2009, compared to 2008, primarily reflects growth in rebates under the U.S. Medicaid program attributable to increasing utilization rates and higher statutory discounts.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Surgical</font></font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Global sales of our surgical products declined 2.5% to $1,430 million in the six months ended June 30, 2009, compared to 2008.&#160;&#160;The effect of unfavorable exchange rates decreased global sales of our surgical products 8.2%.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange fluctuations, our sales of surgical products would have
increased 5.7%.&#160;&#160;Higher sales of advanced technology intraocular lenses, monofocal intraocular lenses and cataract and vitreoretinal products (which include surgical equipment, devices and disposable products) accounted for the constant currency growth.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Sales of intraocular lenses decreased 2.2% in the six months ended June 30, 2009 over the same period in 2008.&#160;&#160;Excluding the 8.8% negative effect of foreign exchange fluctuations, intraocular lens sales would have increased 6.6%.&#160;&#160;We continued to see some pressure on cataract procedures and advanced technology intraocular
lenses due to global economic conditions.&#160;&#160;Reported global sales of our advanced technology lenses, such as the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174; </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">ReSTOR</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font> and the <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">AcrySof</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174; </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-STYLE: italic">Toric</font>,
increased 15.9% in the six months ended June 30, 2009 and would have grown 24.4%, without the 8.5% negative effect of foreign exchange fluctuations.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Sales of other surgical products were adversely impacted by exchange rates but grew faster on a constant currency basis in the international markets due to growth of phaco surgery in emerging markets, increased acceptance of advanced technology products and the introduction of products in additional markets.&#160;&#160;The solid constant
currency sales growth came from most major product categories within the cataract and vitreoretinal segments.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Refractive sales declined 14.5% to $53 million for the six months ended June 30, 2009.&#160;&#160;Refractive sales for 2009 decreased primarily as a result of global economic conditions.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; TEXT-DECORATION: underline">Consumer Eye Care</font></font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Our global consumer eye care sales, consisting of contact lens care solutions, artificial tears and other general eye care products, decreased 7.2% to $401 million in the six months ended June 30, 2009, compared to $432 million in the six months ended June 30, 2008.&#160;&#160;The effect of unfavorable exchange rates decreased global sales
of our consumer eye care products 7.2%.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange fluctuations, our sales of consumer eye care products would have been even with the prior year.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Sales of our contact lens disinfectants declined 6.3% in the six months ended June 30, 2009 compared to the same period in 2008.&#160;&#160;Excluding the impact of foreign exchange fluctuations, sales of contact lens disinfectants
<br></font></div>
<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div></div>
<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">37</font></div>
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160; </font></div></div>
<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">decreased 1.7%, due to changes in retailer purchasing patterns for our contact lens disinfectants, declines in the market for branded multi-purpose solutions and competitive pressures.</font></div></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">Sales of our artificial tears products decreased 0.7% over the same period in 2008.&#160;&#160;Excluding the effect of foreign exchange fluctuations, sales of our artificial tears products increased 11.0%.&#160;&#160;The increase was primarily due to share gains for our </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic">Systane</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top; FONT-STYLE: italic">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"> product
line.&#160;&#160;A portion of the improvement is due to the launch of </font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic">Systane</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 70%; VERTICAL-ALIGN: text-top">&#174;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic">Ultra</font><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt"> in the United States in</font> <font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">July 2008.</font></font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Gross Profit</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Gross profit decreased 2.4% to $2,401 million in the six months ended June 30, 2009 from $2,459 million in 2008.&#160;&#160;Gross profit increased as a percent of sales to 75.7% in the six months ended June 30, 2009 from 75.2% in 2008.&#160;&#160;Gross profit margin improved as a result of the temporary effect of differences in foreign currency
exchange rates between the first quarters of 2009 and 2008.&#160;&#160;Favorable product sales mix variations and manufacturing efficiencies also contributed to the improvement.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Operating Expenses</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Selling, general and administrative expenses decreased 7.0% to $940 million in the six months ended June 30, 2009 from $1,011 million in 2008.&#160;&#160;Selling, general and administrative expenses decreased as a percentage of sales to 29.6% from 30.9% in 2008.&#160;&#160;In 2009, we experienced the costs of sales force additions in selected
Asian and European countries, as well as lapping costs of prior year sales force additions that took place progressively after the first quarter of 2008 in the United States, Japan and emerging markets to support new product launches and/or increased direct selling share-of-voice competitiveness, and the in-period costs of the reduction in other workforce.&#160;&#160;These costs were more than offset by the favorable effects of foreign currency fluctuations, lower share-based payments expense, and disciplined
cost management programs.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Research and development expenses increased 5.6% to $303 million (or 9.6% of sales) in the six months ended June 30, 2009 from $287 million (or 8.8% of sales) in 2008.&#160;&#160;The increase in research and development expenses represented a continued investment across pharmaceutical, surgical and consumer eye care product lines.&#160;&#160;In-period
costs for reductions in workforce were mostly offset by decreases in share-based payments expense.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Amortization of intangibles decreased to $12 million in the six months ended June 30, 2009, from $15 million in 2008.&#160;&#160;Certain paid-up licenses became fully amortized in 2008, reducing amortization expense.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="justify"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Operating Income</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Operating income remained flat at $1,146 million in the six months ended June 30, 2009, compared to 2008.&#160;&#160;The operating income in 2009 reflected the decrease in gross profit (from lower sales), which was offset by reduced operating expenses discussed above.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Alcon United States business segment operating income increased 3.0% to $828 million, or 57.2% of sales, in the six months ended June 30, 2009 from $804 million, or 55.0% of sales, in 2008.&#160;&#160;Operating income as a percent of sales improved in 2009 as a result of lower operating expenses, in particular spending programs.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Alcon International business segment operating income increased 0.8% to $751 million, or 43.6% of sales, in the six months ended June 30, 2009 from $745 million, or 41.1% of sales in 2008.&#160;&#160;In 2009, the operating income margin improved as result of the temporary effect of differences in foreign currency exchange rates between the
first quarters of 2009 and 2008, favorable product sales mix on gross margin as a percent of sales and improved operating expense ratio leverage.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Operating income for the Alcon United States and Alcon International business segments does not include: (1) certain manufacturing costs (e.g., manufacturing operation period costs and manufacturing variances); (2) research and development costs other than regulatory costs; (3) certain other general corporate expenses; and (4) share-based
compensation.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div id="PGBRK" style="MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt">
<div id="FTR">
<div id="GLFTR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="left">&#160;</div></div>
<div id="PN" style="PAGE-BREAK-AFTER: always">
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">38</font></div>
<div style="WIDTH: 100%; TEXT-ALIGN: center"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 8pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">&#160; </font></div></div>
<div id="HDR">
<div id="GLHDR" style="WIDTH: 100%" align="right">&#160;</div></div></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-WEIGHT: bold; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-STYLE: italic; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Interest and Other Income (Expenses)</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Interest income decreased 47.8% to $24 million in the six months ended June 30, 2009 from $46 million in 2008, primarily as a result of lower short term interest rates, partially offset by slightly higher balances of cash and cash equivalents in 2009.&#160;&#160;Interest expense decreased 68.8% to $10 million in the six months ended June
30, 2009 from $32 million in 2008, resulting from lower borrowings and decreased interest<font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt">&#160;</font>rates.</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; MARGIN-LEFT: 0pt; TEXT-INDENT: 18pt; MARGIN-RIGHT: 0pt" align="left"><font style="DISPLAY: inline; FONT-SIZE: 10pt; FONT-FAMILY: Times New Roman">Other, net, included gains (losses) on investments for the six months ended June 30, 2009 and 2008 as follows:</font></div>
<div style="DISPLAY: block; TEXT-INDENT: 0pt">
<br></div>
<div align="left">
